1
00:00:06,555 --> 00:00:08,520
These are lives we can save.

2
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:10,520
Flowers...

3
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:13,315
Sir Song Jiang...

4
00:00:13,315 --> 00:00:16,275
No longer will I rely
on the heavens to strike.

5
00:00:16,275 --> 00:00:17,865
I will take action myself.

6
00:00:17,865 --> 00:00:20,263
For if heaven refuses to send aid,

7
00:00:20,263 --> 00:00:23,515
then we, the people must act.

8
00:00:23,515 --> 00:00:25,630
Locusts are dangerous pests to keep around.

9
00:00:25,630 --> 00:00:29,240
You share Wang Jin's eyes.

10
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:31,645
The eyes of a locust.

11
00:00:31,645 --> 00:00:34,839
I shall become your first branch.

12
00:00:34,839 --> 00:00:37,949
For starters, a small country will do.

13
00:00:39,242 --> 00:00:40,512
Indeed.

14
00:00:51,751 --> 00:00:53,865
What was your impression of him?

15
00:00:53,865 --> 00:00:55,720
[Song Jiang, Yuncheng Clerk]

16
00:00:55,720 --> 00:00:58,105
Ah, Chao Gai.

17
00:00:58,105 --> 00:01:00,220
Was he as you expected?

18
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:04,400
His face certainly was not.

19
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,630
His face?

20
00:01:05,630 --> 00:01:09,870
I had imagined many sorts of faces
before our meeting.

21
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:12,845
But none matched the one
who appeared before me.

22
00:01:12,845 --> 00:01:16,555
If I had to say...
[Chao Gai, Bandit King]

23
00:01:16,555 --> 00:01:21,445
His face left me excited for the future.

24
00:01:24,084 --> 00:01:27,946
I feel my blood...
[Lu Zhi Shen, Monk]

25
00:01:27,946 --> 00:01:31,036
being set ablaze.

26
00:01:33,455 --> 00:01:34,940
What's wrong?

27
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:36,745
Does he irk you?
[Ruan Xiao Wu, Fisherman]

28
00:01:36,745 --> 00:01:40,065
You always mull in silence
when you're bothered, Brother.

29
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:47,680
Tell our comrades across the land
of this development.

30
00:01:48,910 --> 00:01:52,790
We shall set this country in motion.

31
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:29,020
[Dongjing Kaifeng, Capital of Northern Song]

32
00:02:38,687 --> 00:02:42,347
[Episode 2]

33
00:02:46,015 --> 00:02:48,130
Where is Sir Yuan Ming?
[Li Fu, Insurgence Advisor]

34
00:02:48,130 --> 00:02:50,476
He has yet to arrive.

35
00:02:50,476 --> 00:02:52,131
Is that so.

36
00:02:52,131 --> 00:02:54,240
How are the Imperial Guards?

37
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,260
Is it terrible, Li Fu.
[Cang Ying, Military Advisor]

38
00:02:56,260 --> 00:03:01,480
Marshall Tong Guan
insists on re-training the guards.

39
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:07,646
He only wishes to have strong warriors
at his beck and call.

40
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:10,821
As a eunuch, I suppose
nothing else pleasures him.

41
00:03:10,821 --> 00:03:14,501
This is no place for sharing complaints.

42
00:03:17,465 --> 00:03:20,640
Tong Guan has always been an odd fellow

43
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:23,470
when it comes to his men and affection.

44
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:29,010
We must remember to align our ambitions
[Qinglian Temple, Intelligence Organization]

45
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:31,830
with that of the ruling chancellor, Cai Jing,

46
00:03:31,830 --> 00:03:38,660
while gripping the reigns from the shadows.

47
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:42,780
Gao Qiu is garnering the emperor's favor.
[Wu Da, Local Militia Advisor]

48
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:47,310
He may prove to be a nuisance to us.

49
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:49,560
That will not happen.

50
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,560
Sir Yuan Ming.

51
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:56,690
Gao Qiu is but a weed sprouted
by the emperor's foot.

52
00:03:56,690 --> 00:03:59,520
We can do away with him at any moment.

53
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:02,020
Now cease the idle chatter.

54
00:04:02,020 --> 00:04:05,350
Make your reports.
[Yuan Ming, Leader of Qinglian Temple]

55
00:04:05,350 --> 00:04:09,940
Over 3,000 bandits occupy Liangshan Marsh.
[He Gong, Civil Affairs Advisor]

56
00:04:09,940 --> 00:04:13,020
Even regional militia
refuse to deal with them.

57
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:15,465
However, these bandits target merchants,

58
00:04:15,465 --> 00:04:17,609
rather than revolt against the country.

59
00:04:17,609 --> 00:04:20,275
It is not logic,

60
00:04:20,275 --> 00:04:24,665
but your spine
which shall alert you to danger.

61
00:04:25,385 --> 00:04:31,310
I have my eyes on many potential rebels, sir.

62
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:34,710
Not because they are logically
a source of danger,

63
00:04:35,495 --> 00:04:38,080
but because they send shivers down my spine.

64
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:41,510
That is the sort of intel I wish to hear.

65
00:04:41,510 --> 00:04:45,819
Then I shall start
by presenting these writings.

66
00:04:45,819 --> 00:04:48,219
"Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name", is it?

67
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:52,090
You are aware of these scripts, sir?

68
00:04:55,255 --> 00:04:58,480
"If heaven refuses to send aid,
then we, the people must act."

69
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:02,165
I agree with the sentiment entirely.

70
00:05:02,165 --> 00:05:03,980
However!

71
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:07,900
One must not destroy the country
in the process.

72
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:10,090
We shall be the ones to take action.

73
00:05:10,090 --> 00:05:17,060
We shall rebuild this nation
from the shadows.

74
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:21,660
I believe those who are moved by this text

75
00:05:21,660 --> 00:05:24,820
will one day become a dangerous ensemble.

76
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:26,790
Then we must quickly extinguish these embers.

77
00:05:26,790 --> 00:05:28,740
Let them smolder.

78
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:32,374
To strengthen the earth,
one must first await a storm.

79
00:05:32,374 --> 00:05:39,404
The presence of a common enemy
will reinvigorate our citizens.

80
00:05:40,095 --> 00:05:44,810
I suspect it will be
a rather bloody storm, at that.

81
00:05:44,810 --> 00:05:48,125
Send our envoys to keep an eye
on these rebels.

82
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:50,065
Yes, sir.

83
00:05:55,795 --> 00:05:58,120
- Li Fu.
- Sir?

84
00:05:58,120 --> 00:06:00,885
I must ask about this salt.

85
00:06:00,885 --> 00:06:07,445
Is it possible these bandits use salt
as the source of their funds?

86
00:06:08,995 --> 00:06:11,610
Yes, sir.

87
00:06:11,610 --> 00:06:14,820
Though the number of bandits only rise,

88
00:06:14,820 --> 00:06:18,620
the amount of smuggled salt remains steady.
[Salt, cannot be traded...]

89
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:21,310
Why do you suspect that is?
[without the country's permission]

90
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:26,850
This salt is smuggled in
through various, ingenious methods.

91
00:06:26,850 --> 00:06:30,750
I believe they trade with utmost caution.

92
00:06:30,750 --> 00:06:32,610
Precisely so.

93
00:06:32,610 --> 00:06:36,450
And what does that suggest, Li Fu?

94
00:06:36,450 --> 00:06:38,795
The one organizing these trade routes

95
00:06:38,795 --> 00:06:42,940
must have a substantial amount of influence.

96
00:06:42,940 --> 00:06:47,380
An individual, like the Pagoda-Shifting
Heavenly King, for example.

97
00:06:48,585 --> 00:06:52,910
What truly sends chills down my spine,

98
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:56,000
is not one anticipated danger.

99
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,290
But two surprising elements merging together,

100
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:03,475
to bring about unprecedented change.

101
00:07:03,475 --> 00:07:06,135
[Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name]

102
00:07:24,466 --> 00:07:27,836
You are as stubborn as they say, Lin Chong.

103
00:07:28,710 --> 00:07:32,190
How do you not see your efforts are in vain?

104
00:07:33,450 --> 00:07:36,210
We already have a country.

105
00:07:36,895 --> 00:07:39,660
What purpose is there
in tearing this nation apart?

106
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:43,560
[Lin Chong, Spearman Instructor]

107
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:49,220
You people can only break.

108
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:52,660
- Continue.
- Yes, sir.

109
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:10,190
[Huazhou]

110
00:08:13,452 --> 00:08:17,769
Mother, are you alright?

111
00:08:17,769 --> 00:08:23,010
I am fine, my son.
[Wang Jin, Martial Arts Instructor]

112
00:08:23,795 --> 00:08:29,550
The further we trek,
[Madam Wang, Wang Jin's mother]

113
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:33,390
the further you escape from death's grip.

114
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:40,210
As your mother, that is my utmost priority.

115
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:49,310
Mother!

116
00:08:52,095 --> 00:08:55,200
I thank you for your help.

117
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,700
Of course.

118
00:08:57,700 --> 00:09:06,380
But Wang Jin,
you must let your mother rest here.

119
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:07,950
Pardon?

120
00:09:07,950 --> 00:09:10,615
I can tell her organs are growing weak.

121
00:09:10,615 --> 00:09:13,615
Her expression betrays herself.

122
00:09:14,406 --> 00:09:20,056
I suppose my mother always
was a stubborn woman.

123
00:09:22,295 --> 00:09:25,820
If you will allow us,
then I shall take up your kind offer.

124
00:09:25,820 --> 00:09:32,274
I wish my son could meet you both.
[Shi Li, Chief of Shi Family Village]

125
00:09:32,274 --> 00:09:34,460
Your son?

126
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:39,000
He lost his mother when he was only six,

127
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:44,880
and has since dedicated his life
to honing his strength.

128
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:47,170
Is that not a respectable path to take?

129
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:52,375
Perhaps, if my son was not such a ruffian,

130
00:09:52,375 --> 00:09:55,415
seeking only to grow ever stronger.
[Shi Jin, Shi Li's son]

131
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:05,590
Why must we bury Father here?

132
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:15,800
Your father worked under Song Jiang.

133
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:21,360
His death cannot be made known.

134
00:10:22,305 --> 00:10:25,380
We cannot even give him a grave?

135
00:10:25,380 --> 00:10:28,020
You need not know any more.
[Ma Gui, Song Jiang's spy]

136
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:34,300
Mother...
[Yan Po Xi, Yan Xin's daughter]

137
00:10:35,730 --> 00:10:37,580
Po Xi.

138
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:43,330
We must survive.

139
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:45,810
Steel your heart for what is to come.

140
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,140
I am sending you away...

141
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:53,880
to be Song Jiang's mistress.

142
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:57,970
Mother?

143
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,720
Pardon me, sir.

144
00:11:11,020 --> 00:11:13,730
You have a visitor.
[Tang Niu Er, Song Jiang's assistant]

145
00:11:21,910 --> 00:11:24,090
Yan Po Xi?

146
00:11:26,190 --> 00:11:28,750
My, you've grown.

147
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:31,940
What brings you here at this hour?

148
00:11:44,540 --> 00:11:48,760
Po Xi? What are you doing?

149
00:11:51,465 --> 00:11:53,520
Tang Niu Er.

150
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:56,180
- Tang Niu Er!
- Y-Yes, sir!

151
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:35,040
Why do you cry?

152
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:45,640
My father has died.

153
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:52,410
And my mother, she told me to steel myself.

154
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:58,420
Is that why you have come here?

155
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:05,660
What a fool.

156
00:13:07,820 --> 00:13:14,500
Your father was a loyal subordinate of mine.

157
00:13:15,335 --> 00:13:19,650
Did you think
I would so easily abandon his family?

158
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:25,050
My mother said we must survive.

159
00:13:31,490 --> 00:13:33,250
Po Xi.

160
00:13:34,185 --> 00:13:38,170
I desire to create a world

161
00:13:38,170 --> 00:13:43,200
where no such tragedies
are expected to occur.

162
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:47,810
Create... a world?

163
00:14:04,575 --> 00:14:09,390
I know. You will become my attendant.

164
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:12,305
Surely that will put you at ease.

165
00:14:12,305 --> 00:14:14,025
Do not worry any more.

166
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:36,520
Give me pork, veggies,
[Wang Lun, Head of Liangshan Marsh]

167
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,617
and some buns, Pops.
[Wang Lun, Head of Liangshan Marsh]

168
00:14:39,305 --> 00:14:41,850
[Zhu Gui, Eatery Proprietor]

169
00:14:41,850 --> 00:14:43,640
You've returned.

170
00:14:44,935 --> 00:14:48,060
You look displeased to see me.

171
00:14:48,060 --> 00:14:53,880
We once fought side-by-side
to change this country, did we not?

172
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:56,700
And now we've both lost such ambitions.

173
00:14:56,700 --> 00:15:00,160
I ask for food, not harassment.

174
00:15:02,975 --> 00:15:05,460
That looks delicious.

175
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:09,290
Zhu Gui, give me what he is having.

176
00:15:14,230 --> 00:15:16,180
You damned perverted man.

177
00:15:23,675 --> 00:15:28,820
You once pledged to rid this country
of corruption.

178
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:30,940
Where has that man gone?

179
00:15:32,785 --> 00:15:37,020
My ambitions have grown, old friend.

180
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:40,870
Zhu Gui.

181
00:15:41,620 --> 00:15:45,730
Only you are allowed to wield a weapon...

182
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:50,510
in my presence.

183
00:15:56,305 --> 00:15:59,460
A gift, you say?

184
00:15:59,460 --> 00:16:03,790
Yes. I would never visit empty-handed.

185
00:16:04,805 --> 00:16:07,980
Is this eatery as good as you claim?

186
00:16:07,980 --> 00:16:10,740
Indeed. It is a recent favorite of mine.

187
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:14,881
Still, why must you go to visit them?

188
00:16:14,881 --> 00:16:17,336
They ought to come to you.

189
00:16:17,336 --> 00:16:21,711
You are not Chao Gai's subordinate.

190
00:16:21,711 --> 00:16:23,900
He is a wanted man,

191
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:26,355
while I am a countryside clerk.

192
00:16:26,355 --> 00:16:30,665
Which of us would draw less attention
in the streets?

193
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:33,910
The answer is an obvious one.

194
00:16:40,845 --> 00:16:44,160
Thank you for always visiting.

195
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,705
Of course.

196
00:16:45,705 --> 00:16:49,760
[Chen Li, Zhu Gui's wife]

197
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:51,640
I'll be back.

198
00:16:52,980 --> 00:16:54,850
Apologies, sir.

199
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,630
Good afternoon.

200
00:17:07,095 --> 00:17:09,510
Welcome, Song Jiang. Do you require a seat?

201
00:17:09,510 --> 00:17:12,330
No, I have come to purchase a gift.

202
00:17:12,330 --> 00:17:15,380
May I have some of your delicious
seafood buns?

203
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:17,490
Of course.

204
00:17:17,490 --> 00:17:19,550
How many are we feeding?

205
00:17:19,550 --> 00:17:20,900
I would not know.

206
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:23,785
I will take as many as you can offer.

207
00:17:23,785 --> 00:17:25,315
Coming right up.

208
00:17:30,342 --> 00:17:35,150
My wife has been ill for some time now.

209
00:17:35,150 --> 00:17:36,750
I have heard.

210
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:40,691
The fishermen in this area
sing high praises of her.

211
00:17:40,691 --> 00:17:43,031
She is a kind woman.

212
00:17:44,965 --> 00:17:48,700
I know a bit about medicinal herbs.

213
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:50,630
I will bring some next time I visit.

214
00:17:50,630 --> 00:17:52,781
I appreciate your concern, Sir Song Jiang.

215
00:17:52,781 --> 00:17:56,701
But a number of doctors
have already visited my wife.

216
00:17:58,425 --> 00:18:00,620
Is that so.

217
00:18:00,620 --> 00:18:03,060
I, too, wish I could do more.

218
00:18:06,835 --> 00:18:11,450
I apologize for making an unnecessary remark.

219
00:18:11,450 --> 00:18:13,190
No, not at all.

220
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:20,560
Will this suffice to feed your crowd?

221
00:18:23,466 --> 00:18:26,146
- Yes, thank you.
- It is my pleasure.

222
00:18:32,875 --> 00:18:36,790
Chief! Chief!

223
00:18:36,790 --> 00:18:38,810
What is this commotion about?

224
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:42,260
He brings trouble!

225
00:18:43,765 --> 00:18:47,830
What do scum like you
want from my villa?

226
00:18:47,830 --> 00:18:50,605
I'll break your legs till you can't walk.

227
00:18:50,605 --> 00:18:53,225
Come at me all at once.

228
00:18:56,710 --> 00:18:58,960
What is this commotion?

229
00:19:06,860 --> 00:19:09,980
Unhand me!

230
00:19:18,940 --> 00:19:21,230
Foolish.

231
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,040
You there.

232
00:19:25,985 --> 00:19:27,810
Did you call me a fool?

233
00:19:27,810 --> 00:19:30,880
It is unhanding your weapon
that I find foolish.

234
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:33,764
As if you could best me.

235
00:19:33,764 --> 00:19:38,029
You have grown drunk on your own strength.

236
00:19:38,029 --> 00:19:42,799
You belittle, and look down on your foes.

237
00:19:43,940 --> 00:19:45,950
An utter fool.

238
00:19:46,735 --> 00:19:52,450
You are fated to die on the battlefield.

239
00:19:52,450 --> 00:19:54,190
Me?

240
00:19:55,525 --> 00:19:59,160
The Nine Tattooed Dragons, dying in battle?

241
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,515
Come, fight me.

242
00:20:00,515 --> 00:20:03,875
I only gave an explanation
because I was asked.

243
00:20:04,625 --> 00:20:07,520
I would never injure
the son of a village chief.

244
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:09,675
I will humbly decline your duel.

245
00:20:09,675 --> 00:20:11,615
I do not mind.

246
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:13,870
Chief Shi Li.

247
00:20:13,870 --> 00:20:15,940
If my son breaks a bone or two,

248
00:20:15,940 --> 00:20:21,720
that is his own fault to bear.

249
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:26,510
Please humble this arrogant brat.

250
00:20:27,375 --> 00:20:29,660
Are you certain, sir?

251
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:34,790
He must learn a lesson, through combat.

252
00:20:35,915 --> 00:20:39,080
Then I shall do my part,
to repay your generosity.

253
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:41,070
Enough slander.

254
00:20:43,015 --> 00:20:46,780
I will keep his injuries to a minimum.

255
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:48,780
Wait.

256
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:51,265
If you're facing me, use a proper staff.

257
00:20:51,265 --> 00:20:56,865
Or do you intend to disrespect
the Nine Tattooed Dragons further?

258
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:02,860
This piece of firewood
will more than suffice against you.

259
00:21:03,790 --> 00:21:07,910
If you are dissatisfied,
then prove yourself by besting me once.

260
00:21:17,135 --> 00:21:19,830
You are Ruan Xiao Wu, yes?

261
00:21:19,830 --> 00:21:23,000
Where might Chao Gai be?

262
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:29,000
Thank you very much.

263
00:21:30,745 --> 00:21:32,200
[Wu Yong, Private Tutor]

264
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:35,500
My name is Wu Yong. Please, follow me.

265
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:38,390
"Timely Rain".

266
00:21:39,185 --> 00:21:40,500
That's your nickname, right?

267
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,475
[Timely Rain]

268
00:21:42,475 --> 00:21:45,645
Indeed, some call me that.

269
00:21:49,790 --> 00:21:55,430
"Timely Rain".
Rain that falls when most inopportune.

270
00:21:59,035 --> 00:22:01,310
What of it?

271
00:22:01,310 --> 00:22:03,795
Nothing.

272
00:22:03,795 --> 00:22:09,320
When it rains, I reckon you use an umbrella.

273
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:14,190
While we cling to our boats for dear life.

274
00:22:16,635 --> 00:22:18,870
I'm afraid I do not follow.

275
00:22:18,870 --> 00:22:24,792
Even something like rain is different
for you clerks, versus us fishermen.

276
00:22:24,792 --> 00:22:28,632
Is that not true, "Timely Rain"?

277
00:22:35,190 --> 00:22:37,655
On rainy days,

278
00:22:37,655 --> 00:22:41,037
I rush around the village,
worrying for our crops.

279
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:47,050
On stormy days,
I worry for the integrity of our homes.

280
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:52,960
On rainy days following a drought,
I feel relief.

281
00:22:54,045 --> 00:23:00,070
It is true, we all perceive rain
in different ways.

282
00:23:00,070 --> 00:23:05,915
And you have just taught me
the dangers of rain atop a boat.

283
00:23:05,915 --> 00:23:08,720
I will continue to learn
from these differences,

284
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:12,660
and gather the hearts of many within me.

285
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:18,410
Will that not suffice, Ruan Xiao Wu?

286
00:23:37,025 --> 00:23:41,310
A daytime shower? How mysterious.

287
00:23:41,310 --> 00:23:43,095
Wu Da.

288
00:23:43,095 --> 00:23:45,435
What is on your mind?

289
00:23:46,425 --> 00:23:52,400
I was simply recalling
a sentiment expressed by Yuan Ming.

290
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:54,000
What sentiment, if I may ask?

291
00:23:55,650 --> 00:23:59,490
When two surprising elements merge together,

292
00:23:59,490 --> 00:24:02,630
they bring about unprecedented change.

293
00:24:05,910 --> 00:24:08,970
Just like this daytime shower here.

294
00:24:25,110 --> 00:24:27,000
Master Lin Chong.

295
00:24:27,730 --> 00:24:31,970
You are Master Lin Chong, are you not?

296
00:24:37,065 --> 00:24:38,690
Who...

297
00:24:38,690 --> 00:24:41,120
I am not surprised you have forgotten.

298
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:45,080
I am one of your many disciples.

299
00:24:46,125 --> 00:24:47,400
Disciples?

300
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:50,175
You trained me rough.

301
00:24:50,175 --> 00:24:52,605
Enough to have me pass out.

302
00:24:53,330 --> 00:24:56,361
To see you reduced to scraps...

303
00:24:56,361 --> 00:24:58,370
What a pity.

304
00:24:59,082 --> 00:25:02,650
You must be parched, no?

305
00:25:02,650 --> 00:25:05,940
They've starved you for three days now.

306
00:25:05,940 --> 00:25:08,790
Here. Have some water.

307
00:25:10,390 --> 00:25:12,000
Water?

308
00:25:13,975 --> 00:25:15,710
Here, here.

309
00:25:15,710 --> 00:25:17,635
Drink up.

310
00:25:17,635 --> 00:25:19,155
Water.

311
00:25:24,410 --> 00:25:29,160
Why do you retch? I added plenty of salt.

312
00:25:32,665 --> 00:25:34,490
Why...

313
00:25:34,490 --> 00:25:36,540
Why?

314
00:26:02,940 --> 00:26:05,080
I do not even need this firewood.

315
00:26:06,230 --> 00:26:07,950
My bare hands will be plenty.

316
00:26:20,975 --> 00:26:25,440
Those drunk on their own strength
are fated to lose their lives.

317
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,960
Has our spar sobered you?

318
00:26:28,797 --> 00:26:32,142
I had a feeling you were no ordinary fellow,

319
00:26:32,142 --> 00:26:37,992
yet you have far exceeded my expectations.

320
00:26:39,650 --> 00:26:44,120
I suppose I am obligated to speak the truth.

321
00:26:48,455 --> 00:26:52,280
I formerly trained the Imperial Guard.

322
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:55,725
I am currently on the run
for reasons I must not disclose.

323
00:26:55,725 --> 00:26:57,855
The Imperial Guard...

324
00:26:58,805 --> 00:27:01,190
No wonder you are so strong.

325
00:27:01,190 --> 00:27:05,950
Rest assured, I did nothing to be ashamed of.

326
00:27:06,990 --> 00:27:11,166
Still, I cannot impose on you any longer.

327
00:27:12,007 --> 00:27:15,239
My mother and I shall leave tonight.

328
00:27:16,375 --> 00:27:18,610
Please, make me your disciple!

329
00:27:18,610 --> 00:27:20,250
Say what?

330
00:27:21,730 --> 00:27:23,890
You, my disciple?

331
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:35,250
I would like to discuss our plan
to seize Liangshan Marsh.

332
00:27:35,250 --> 00:27:38,375
- I see.
- What do you think we most require?

333
00:27:38,375 --> 00:27:43,287
Soldiers, weapons, and a commander, yes?

334
00:27:43,287 --> 00:27:47,890
Indeed. But I am asking a simpler question.

335
00:27:47,890 --> 00:27:51,220
Eat. We will speak shortly.

336
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:54,830
You're here.

337
00:27:55,690 --> 00:27:58,980
This is Song Jiang.

338
00:28:00,745 --> 00:28:02,400
I am Lu Jun Yi.
[Lu Jun Yi, Distributor of smuggled salt]

339
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:05,390
This is Yan Qing.
[Lu Jun Yi, Distributor of smuggled salt]

340
00:28:05,390 --> 00:28:07,810
[Yan Qing, Lu Jun Yi's attendant]

341
00:28:08,660 --> 00:28:10,600
"Lu Jun Yi"?

342
00:28:11,455 --> 00:28:15,690
The greatest merchant of Da Ming, Beijing?

343
00:28:15,690 --> 00:28:17,190
You have heard my name?

344
00:28:17,190 --> 00:28:20,270
Of course!
Your accolades speak for themselves!

345
00:28:20,270 --> 00:28:23,345
Your high praise honors me, good sir.

346
00:28:23,345 --> 00:28:28,591
I have called Lu Jun Yi
to help solidify our plans.

347
00:28:28,591 --> 00:28:32,250
We must talk money.

348
00:28:32,250 --> 00:28:34,295
Money?

349
00:28:34,295 --> 00:28:38,427
Money. Coins. Gold.

350
00:28:39,230 --> 00:28:41,410
Call it what you will.

351
00:28:43,670 --> 00:28:45,240
Lu Jun Yi.

352
00:28:54,316 --> 00:28:59,031
Song Jiang, do you know what this is?

353
00:29:12,580 --> 00:29:15,000
I believe that is salt.

354
00:29:18,165 --> 00:29:21,150
- And wonderful salt, at that.
- Indeed.

355
00:29:21,150 --> 00:29:26,245
Yet to the eyes of us merchants,

356
00:29:26,245 --> 00:29:30,115
each granule here is a speck of gold.

357
00:29:31,530 --> 00:29:34,960
Human beings cannot thrive without salt.

358
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:38,577
Salt is the embodiment of money.

359
00:29:40,035 --> 00:29:41,850
Precisely.

360
00:29:41,850 --> 00:29:45,100
Every dish known to man uses salt.

361
00:29:45,100 --> 00:29:47,960
These buns use salt.

362
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:50,810
Preserved foods use salt.

363
00:29:50,810 --> 00:29:54,190
Rations use salt.

364
00:29:54,190 --> 00:29:56,950
Salt is a necessity for survival!

365
00:29:56,950 --> 00:30:01,070
We use salt to preserve
the heads of our enemies.

366
00:30:01,070 --> 00:30:04,650
We use salt to keep our horses running.

367
00:30:04,650 --> 00:30:09,120
Salt. Salt. Salt!

368
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:14,660
Salt makes this world go round.

369
00:30:14,660 --> 00:30:20,125
Yet we cannot acquire salt so freely.

370
00:30:20,125 --> 00:30:24,245
Indeed. The nation keeps a monopoly on salt.

371
00:30:25,475 --> 00:30:28,860
I see now. This salt has been smuggled in.

372
00:30:28,860 --> 00:30:30,750
Correct.

373
00:30:31,538 --> 00:30:37,120
Chao Gai, you have been
circulating this salt?

374
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:42,070
No. It is Lu Jun Yi
who controls the salt roads.

375
00:30:43,045 --> 00:30:49,150
So this is where the master merchant
comes into play.

376
00:30:49,150 --> 00:30:52,450
How exactly do you transport this salt?

377
00:30:52,450 --> 00:30:54,810
Every route has an official who checks cargo.

378
00:30:54,810 --> 00:30:56,145
Do you come in by sea?

379
00:30:56,145 --> 00:30:59,455
No, even then, there are checkpoints.

380
00:31:01,495 --> 00:31:06,810
Ships utilize bags of dirt
to remain steady in rough waters.

381
00:31:06,810 --> 00:31:10,040
Otherwise, they would all easily capsize.

382
00:31:11,560 --> 00:31:16,220
Strangely enough, these foolish officials...

383
00:31:20,338 --> 00:31:21,635
Apologies.

384
00:31:22,825 --> 00:31:24,980
I do not mind.

385
00:31:24,980 --> 00:31:28,190
Plenty of us officials are fools.

386
00:31:28,190 --> 00:31:32,005
These officials will check our cargo,

387
00:31:32,005 --> 00:31:34,645
but not the anchoring dirt bags below.

388
00:31:38,230 --> 00:31:42,000
Impossible. Are those bags filled
not with dirt, but with salt?

389
00:31:43,585 --> 00:31:45,810
The human brain works in mysterious ways.

390
00:31:45,810 --> 00:31:48,230
If they think it is dirt,
then it cannot be salt.

391
00:31:48,230 --> 00:31:50,565
If they do not think it is salt...

392
00:31:50,565 --> 00:31:52,975
Then they would never know it to be money.

393
00:31:53,705 --> 00:32:01,920
Lu Jun Yi has routed several paths
and methods for his salt to be carried.

394
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:10,398
Those who transport my salt
do not realize they are accomplices.

395
00:32:10,398 --> 00:32:14,093
Even if this salt is somehow confiscated,

396
00:32:14,093 --> 00:32:16,440
it cannot be traced back to myself.

397
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:20,320
All routes and inventory of salt

398
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:25,175
remain solely inside of Lu Jun Yi's head.

399
00:32:25,175 --> 00:32:27,815
He has written no note of it anywhere.

400
00:32:29,110 --> 00:32:33,300
Chao Gai, you are a brilliant man.

401
00:32:35,205 --> 00:32:38,310
Wang Lun, the head of Liangshan Marsh,

402
00:32:38,310 --> 00:32:43,547
once hoped to change this corrupted nation.

403
00:32:43,547 --> 00:32:49,617
Yet it is because they struggled financially
that they turned to thievery.

404
00:32:51,205 --> 00:32:53,770
But you are different.

405
00:32:53,770 --> 00:32:55,940
You see the future.

406
00:32:55,940 --> 00:33:00,085
With salt alone, you rally soldiers,
purchase provisions,

407
00:33:00,085 --> 00:33:07,065
and will seize Liangshan Marsh itself.

408
00:33:07,810 --> 00:33:11,950
Chao Gai, you are indeed a brilliant man!

409
00:33:14,015 --> 00:33:16,555
Enough praising, I say.

410
00:33:17,655 --> 00:33:19,520
Here.

411
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:20,950
Eat.

412
00:33:21,650 --> 00:33:23,120
Go on.

413
00:33:48,730 --> 00:33:50,710
Do I pique your curiosity?

414
00:33:52,125 --> 00:33:55,350
I just wondered what you were doing.

415
00:33:55,350 --> 00:33:58,810
I am transcribing Song Jiang's writings.

416
00:33:58,810 --> 00:34:00,755
[Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name]

417
00:34:00,755 --> 00:34:03,205
"Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name", huh?

418
00:34:04,310 --> 00:34:08,420
Here. You may have a copy.

419
00:34:12,780 --> 00:34:18,790
I don't need anything from a cowardly clerk,
nor a hulking monk.

420
00:34:20,245 --> 00:34:22,190
Is that so?

421
00:34:22,190 --> 00:34:24,200
Then I shan't push.

422
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:29,005
[Enforcing the Way in Heaven's Name]

423
00:34:29,005 --> 00:34:31,245
I see you do not admonish him.

424
00:34:33,035 --> 00:34:38,620
When searching for Song Jiang,
he was always seen with a suspicious giant.

425
00:34:38,620 --> 00:34:43,770
Yes, I do tend to stand out.

426
00:34:43,770 --> 00:34:47,600
I must admit,

427
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:52,710
you are nothing like the tales I heard.

428
00:34:52,710 --> 00:34:54,620
How so?

429
00:34:54,620 --> 00:35:00,030
For one, you would not forgive
Ruan Xiao Wu's insolence just now.

430
00:35:00,030 --> 00:35:03,100
Perhaps back when I was a ruffian, yes.

431
00:35:03,100 --> 00:35:08,675
But I have changed, thanks to Song Jiang.

432
00:35:08,675 --> 00:35:12,890
Humans change, time and time again.

433
00:35:14,050 --> 00:35:15,940
Is that not right?

434
00:35:15,940 --> 00:35:18,065
I can only hope so.

435
00:35:18,065 --> 00:35:21,395
And now that you've reformed,
you copy writings all day.

436
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:34,545
What is it you are doing?

437
00:35:34,545 --> 00:35:36,230
What do you mean?

438
00:35:36,230 --> 00:35:40,540
I am transcribing these writings
for the greater good of this nation.

439
00:35:41,505 --> 00:35:44,390
What are you doing?

440
00:35:44,390 --> 00:35:47,400
- I transport salt.
- Salt.

441
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:51,380
I cannot understand why Sir Chao Gai
is so partial towards that clerk.

442
00:35:51,380 --> 00:35:53,850
- Do you dislike officials?
- Huh?

443
00:35:53,850 --> 00:35:56,150
- Song Jiang is different.
- All officials are the same.

444
00:35:56,150 --> 00:36:00,270
Then is Chao Gai the same as other bandits?

445
00:36:00,270 --> 00:36:01,730
No!

446
00:36:01,730 --> 00:36:04,085
You will come to understand.

447
00:36:04,085 --> 00:36:08,918
Spend days, months with him,

448
00:36:08,918 --> 00:36:10,938
and you will understand.

449
00:36:12,330 --> 00:36:14,330
Like hell I will.

450
00:36:23,990 --> 00:36:26,949
I wish to learn from you.

451
00:36:26,949 --> 00:36:32,379
True strength will come
at the risk of your life.

452
00:36:34,310 --> 00:36:36,120
I do not mind.

453
00:36:36,955 --> 00:36:39,000
You will need to overcome death's limits.

454
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,675
[Death's limits]

455
00:36:40,675 --> 00:36:45,536
A practical impossibility
for a man like yourself.

456
00:36:45,536 --> 00:36:47,386
"Death's limits"?

457
00:36:48,915 --> 00:36:51,980
It is to go beyond your very limits.

458
00:36:51,980 --> 00:36:54,450
To experience what lies ahead...

459
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:57,740
when you feel as though you will collapse.

460
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:04,080
Past these limits, movements come with ease.

461
00:37:05,190 --> 00:37:07,830
Your body moves exactly as you will it.

462
00:37:08,865 --> 00:37:11,020
That is the reward
for overcoming death's limit.

463
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:17,435
Then please, guide me to that limit.

464
00:37:17,435 --> 00:37:19,855
I will overcome whatever it imposes on me.

465
00:37:21,310 --> 00:37:23,160
You said you were named "Jin", yes?

466
00:37:24,780 --> 00:37:27,040
We share a name.

467
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:31,620
The road ahead will be excruciating, Shi Jin.

468
00:37:31,620 --> 00:37:34,830
You will curse our encounter every day.

469
00:37:36,190 --> 00:37:38,380
I am prepared for the consequences.

470
00:37:39,356 --> 00:37:45,006
Then I shall impart to you...

471
00:37:46,100 --> 00:37:48,250
the technique of my arts.

472
00:38:01,715 --> 00:38:03,650
Good morning, Tang Niu Er.

473
00:38:03,650 --> 00:38:06,200
Yan Po Xi!

474
00:38:08,375 --> 00:38:11,520
Good morning, Sir Song Jiang!

475
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:14,270
Po Xi? Good morning.

476
00:38:14,270 --> 00:38:15,940
Are you heading out?

477
00:38:15,940 --> 00:38:18,730
Yes, I have some fishing to do.

478
00:38:18,730 --> 00:38:20,250
Fishing?

479
00:38:20,250 --> 00:38:21,440
When will you return?

480
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:23,980
I believe I may be late.

481
00:38:23,980 --> 00:38:26,545
You are free to leave before I return.

482
00:38:26,545 --> 00:38:29,285
Please, take me with you.

483
00:38:30,125 --> 00:38:34,460
That, I cannot do. I am meeting a friend.

484
00:38:34,460 --> 00:38:38,515
Is that "friend" a woman?

485
00:38:38,515 --> 00:38:40,628
No, no.

486
00:38:41,820 --> 00:38:46,210
Is that so. I hope you manage to fish lots.

487
00:38:48,940 --> 00:38:51,070
I will.

488
00:38:56,995 --> 00:38:59,070
Not a bite to be had.

489
00:38:59,070 --> 00:39:00,435
Perhaps you chose a poor spot?

490
00:39:00,435 --> 00:39:05,065
That can't be. This is the season for fish.

491
00:39:07,150 --> 00:39:11,880
So tell me, how do you intend
to fish up that catch?

492
00:39:23,105 --> 00:39:26,940
Springing an attack on the unknown
is suicide.

493
00:39:26,940 --> 00:39:33,675
Across the marsh is a natural fortress,
guarded by cliffs on every side.

494
00:39:33,675 --> 00:39:37,905
A fortress, home to 3,000 bandits.

495
00:39:39,245 --> 00:39:42,410
We cannot rely on a frontal assault.

496
00:39:42,410 --> 00:39:46,560
We will need to attack from within.

497
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:52,290
You plan on making connections with Wang Lun?

498
00:39:52,976 --> 00:39:59,100
Indeed. But I hear Wang Lun
is a cautious man.

499
00:39:59,100 --> 00:40:02,040
None claim to even know his face.

500
00:40:03,455 --> 00:40:07,070
There is one man who does.

501
00:40:07,070 --> 00:40:08,900
Who?

502
00:40:08,900 --> 00:40:12,435
The proprietor of an eatery
next to Liangshan Marsh.

503
00:40:12,435 --> 00:40:19,055
You may know him,
seeing as you bought buns from his place.

504
00:40:19,055 --> 00:40:20,860
Zhu Gui?

505
00:40:20,860 --> 00:40:24,481
He once worked alongside Wang Lun.

506
00:40:24,481 --> 00:40:26,711
I hear they still meet from time to time.

507
00:40:27,886 --> 00:40:35,889
Song Jiang, will you convince Zhu Gui
to aid us in reaching Wang Lun?

508
00:40:37,850 --> 00:40:39,800
Me?

509
00:40:41,085 --> 00:40:45,620
If Wang Lun shares our ambitions,

510
00:40:45,620 --> 00:40:47,630
then we can recruit him to our cause.

511
00:40:47,630 --> 00:40:50,715
If he is but a bandit king,

512
00:40:50,715 --> 00:40:55,275
then we can kill Wang Lun,
and take his fortress for ourselves.

513
00:40:57,020 --> 00:40:59,620
Will it really be so simple?

514
00:41:01,535 --> 00:41:03,560
It will.

515
00:41:03,560 --> 00:41:05,410
For us, it will.

516
00:41:14,247 --> 00:41:17,850
I would like a symbol for our cause.

517
00:41:17,850 --> 00:41:21,000
Song Jiang, do us the honors.

518
00:41:27,390 --> 00:41:31,660
What shall I write?

519
00:41:36,620 --> 00:41:38,830
Fresh catch!

520
00:41:41,150 --> 00:41:43,120
No wonder I had no bites.

521
00:41:47,310 --> 00:41:49,430
I must decline.

522
00:41:50,240 --> 00:41:52,535
Zhu Gui...

523
00:41:52,535 --> 00:41:57,610
I do not wish to associate
with Liangshan Marsh any further.

524
00:41:57,610 --> 00:42:03,472
Song Jiang, I thought
you were an upstanding man.

525
00:42:03,472 --> 00:42:06,002
Will you turn to thievery as well?

526
00:42:07,986 --> 00:42:12,110
Zhu Gui, I have a dream.

527
00:42:12,110 --> 00:42:15,625
I wish to rid this nation of its corruption.

528
00:42:15,625 --> 00:42:18,350
Rid it of corruption.

529
00:42:18,350 --> 00:42:23,509
That man once had the same ambitions.

530
00:42:23,509 --> 00:42:26,049
His words had a certain truth to them.

531
00:42:26,049 --> 00:42:28,949
That is why I lent Wang Lun a hand.

532
00:42:29,875 --> 00:42:35,276
Yet as his numbers and troops grew,

533
00:42:35,276 --> 00:42:39,086
he began to plunder
rich travelers and merchants.

534
00:42:39,849 --> 00:42:41,790
Eventually,

535
00:42:41,790 --> 00:42:45,690
his frustration at failing the civil exam
began to overtake him.

536
00:42:45,690 --> 00:42:49,675
All at once, his motives changed

537
00:42:49,675 --> 00:42:52,605
from his old ambitions, to seeking revenge.

538
00:42:53,406 --> 00:42:57,766
Wang Lun is no longer the man I once knew.

539
00:43:01,590 --> 00:43:04,540
We will not tread the same path as he did.

540
00:43:07,190 --> 00:43:09,950
I can hear it.

541
00:43:09,950 --> 00:43:12,345
Another voice within me.

542
00:43:12,345 --> 00:43:14,445
What does it say?

543
00:43:16,500 --> 00:43:20,290
It suspects you are cut
from the same cloth as he.

544
00:43:26,060 --> 00:43:30,800
My wife is now my sole priority.

545
00:43:32,310 --> 00:43:36,410
I wish to dedicate my life to her,
and her alone.

546
00:43:40,370 --> 00:43:42,250
I understand.

547
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:45,460
I shall push no further.

548
00:43:57,165 --> 00:44:00,600
What? Lin Chong is still alive?
[Gao Qiu, General of the Imperial Guard]

549
00:44:00,600 --> 00:44:04,100
Yes, sir. Sir Li Fu's orders.

550
00:44:04,100 --> 00:44:06,965
And I ordered you to kill him!

551
00:44:06,965 --> 00:44:13,275
A man who aims for my neck
is being kept alive? Unacceptable!

552
00:44:14,915 --> 00:44:18,870
Transfer Lin Chong to another prison.

553
00:44:18,870 --> 00:44:20,190
Pardon?

554
00:44:20,190 --> 00:44:26,810
He will die in an "accident" along the way.

555
00:44:26,810 --> 00:44:28,965
Am I clear?

556
00:44:28,965 --> 00:44:31,065
An "accident", is it?

557
00:44:31,715 --> 00:44:33,750
Unbelievable.

558
00:44:33,750 --> 00:44:38,500
The moves of an utter fool
cannot be anticipated.

559
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:43,910
Why not simply play ball with the Emperor?

560
00:44:45,100 --> 00:44:48,200
Damned Gao Qiu!

561
00:44:57,250 --> 00:44:59,330
Hey. Hey!

562
00:45:01,285 --> 00:45:05,730
Did you hear?
Lin Chong is being sent to Cangzhou.

563
00:45:05,730 --> 00:45:07,940
- Why?
- Beats me.

564
00:45:07,940 --> 00:45:11,780
But I hear General Gao Qiu despises him.

565
00:45:11,780 --> 00:45:14,865
Then he will be killed during the transfer?

566
00:45:14,865 --> 00:45:17,035
It's entirely possible.

567
00:45:49,555 --> 00:45:51,650
Great work.

568
00:45:51,650 --> 00:45:54,005
I hope you are not pushing yourself.

569
00:45:54,005 --> 00:45:55,365
Not at all.

570
00:46:00,450 --> 00:46:07,040
Your husband was an excellent subordinate
who gathered intel from all over.

571
00:46:07,715 --> 00:46:14,160
But that is no reason for you
to carry his mantel.

572
00:46:14,160 --> 00:46:19,030
This job is befitting of me, sir.

573
00:46:19,900 --> 00:46:24,350
My daughter... Is Po Xi well?

574
00:46:25,625 --> 00:46:31,250
Indeed. I promised to take her fishing.

575
00:46:31,250 --> 00:46:33,295
She is still a child, that one.

576
00:46:33,295 --> 00:46:36,395
I apologize for the trouble she may cause.

577
00:46:38,856 --> 00:46:45,116
[Lin Chong will be murdered
while being transferred to Cangzhou]

578
00:46:50,990 --> 00:46:53,020
[Lin Chong]

579
00:46:59,310 --> 00:47:02,800
Lin Chong... He will be killed.

580
00:47:06,495 --> 00:47:10,230
Lin Chong will be killed?

581
00:47:10,230 --> 00:47:11,670
Yes.

582
00:47:12,585 --> 00:47:14,850
What to do...

583
00:47:14,850 --> 00:47:16,340
According to our report,

584
00:47:16,340 --> 00:47:19,520
he will be escorted
by ten or so capable guards.

585
00:47:19,520 --> 00:47:22,310
We cannot lose Lin Chong.

586
00:47:22,310 --> 00:47:27,045
Chao Gai, will you lend me some of your men?

587
00:47:27,045 --> 00:47:30,025
Why do we have to save this Lin Chong?

588
00:47:30,926 --> 00:47:33,531
Because all lives are inherently connected.

589
00:47:33,531 --> 00:47:35,060
That's nonsense.

590
00:47:35,060 --> 00:47:37,400
It is not nonsense.

591
00:47:37,400 --> 00:47:40,965
If we save Lin Chong,
we can save a man named An Dao Quan.

592
00:47:40,965 --> 00:47:45,560
If we save An Dao Quan,
we can save Chen Li, and Zhu Gui.

593
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:47,890
This man is crazy in the head.

594
00:47:47,890 --> 00:47:52,360
Song Jiang, you must make yourself clear.

595
00:47:52,360 --> 00:47:54,550
My apologies.

596
00:47:54,550 --> 00:47:57,700
Lin Chong will be transferred to a prison

597
00:47:57,700 --> 00:48:00,020
where a doctor named An Dao Quan is held.

598
00:48:00,020 --> 00:48:03,650
I can personally attest to his skills.

599
00:48:03,650 --> 00:48:05,560
He is able to cure any disease I've seen.

600
00:48:05,560 --> 00:48:08,100
What's so important about this doctor?

601
00:48:08,100 --> 00:48:12,390
That man will be able to cure Zhu Gui's wife.

602
00:48:12,390 --> 00:48:16,980
You will have Zhu Gui repay the favor
by allowing us to see Wang Lun?

603
00:48:16,980 --> 00:48:20,690
No, I earnestly wish to save her life.

604
00:48:20,690 --> 00:48:26,335
Zhu Gui has lost faith in this world of ours.

605
00:48:26,335 --> 00:48:29,065
That is why I wish to remind him.

606
00:48:30,118 --> 00:48:35,308
This world still has
its share of hopeless fools.

607
00:48:37,270 --> 00:48:44,660
Fools, who will risk it all
to save our people.

608
00:48:48,113 --> 00:48:50,573
You're asking me to believe you?

609
00:48:51,205 --> 00:48:58,350
Ruan Xiao Wu. I understand
you respect Chao Gai, and despise me.

610
00:48:58,350 --> 00:49:01,900
While it is true we aim for the same goals,

611
00:49:01,900 --> 00:49:05,350
our methods differ slightly from each other.

612
00:49:05,350 --> 00:49:08,715
Even so, I think that is perfectly fine.

613
00:49:08,715 --> 00:49:11,815
Then allow me to ask you this.

614
00:49:13,440 --> 00:49:16,840
What exactly is this "method" of yours?

615
00:49:19,280 --> 00:49:22,000
To fight, by encroaching on the heart.

616
00:49:22,700 --> 00:49:24,390
Rather...

617
00:49:25,255 --> 00:49:28,730
To fight, by saving hearts.

618
00:49:28,730 --> 00:49:30,910
That is my way.

619
00:49:30,910 --> 00:49:33,520
Bullshit!

620
00:49:33,520 --> 00:49:38,020
What have you done
aside from write this text?

621
00:49:38,020 --> 00:49:40,270
You've only crafted impractical theories.

622
00:49:40,270 --> 00:49:42,305
It's all talk, no action.

623
00:49:42,305 --> 00:49:44,855
Ruan Xiao Wu! You have stepped out of line!

624
00:49:51,245 --> 00:49:56,400
Lin Chong is the only one
who can help that doctor escape.

625
00:49:56,400 --> 00:49:58,100
You still insist on saving this man?

626
00:50:03,020 --> 00:50:07,510
Please, help me in saving Lin Chong.

627
00:50:08,915 --> 00:50:13,110
I wish to rescue Lin Chong, and An Dao Quan.

628
00:50:13,110 --> 00:50:16,883
To cure Chen Li, and help Zhu Gui.

629
00:50:16,883 --> 00:50:21,133
And to save you as well.

630
00:50:23,650 --> 00:50:28,290
Lives are all connected, Ruan Xiao Wu.

631
00:50:30,156 --> 00:50:35,256
This is how you fight, Song Jiang?

632
00:50:53,610 --> 00:50:55,290
Wu Yong.

633
00:51:01,150 --> 00:51:03,540
How do we save Lin Chong?

634
00:51:13,530 --> 00:51:15,450
Ruan Xiao Wu...

635
00:51:21,035 --> 00:51:24,030
[Da Ming, Beijing]

636
00:51:24,030 --> 00:51:29,650
[Cangzhou]

637
00:51:31,850 --> 00:51:36,170
Do not think death will bring peace to you.

638
00:51:39,845 --> 00:51:42,510
Though there are several routes
the guards could take,

639
00:51:42,510 --> 00:51:45,235
I believe they will avoid the valley.

640
00:51:45,235 --> 00:51:47,245
Why?

641
00:51:47,245 --> 00:51:50,150
The valley has no natural guard
against attacks.

642
00:51:50,150 --> 00:51:52,375
They will likely hug the river instead.

643
00:51:52,375 --> 00:51:56,020
Ruan Xiao Wu, depart ahead of time
to keep watch.

644
00:51:56,020 --> 00:51:58,730
Prepare to give a signal
once the guards are in sight.

645
00:51:58,730 --> 00:52:03,060
But do not have your subordinates with you.

646
00:52:03,060 --> 00:52:05,755
We shall strike with a small team.

647
00:52:05,755 --> 00:52:12,215
Chao Gai, Ruan Xiao Wu,
Lu Zhi Shen, and myself will go.

648
00:52:14,435 --> 00:52:16,650
Really, it will be a strike team of three.

649
00:52:16,650 --> 00:52:20,715
Wu Yong is a tactician more than a fighter.

650
00:52:20,715 --> 00:52:23,575
You four will go alone?

651
00:52:23,575 --> 00:52:26,650
No, I shall join you.

652
00:52:26,650 --> 00:52:31,450
Song Jiang, you cannot be seen with Chao Gai.

653
00:52:32,569 --> 00:52:39,804
You must remain an innocent clerk for now.

654
00:52:39,804 --> 00:52:44,354
Leave this sort of dirty work to us.

655
00:52:50,796 --> 00:52:55,950
I promise to return with him, Song Jiang.

656
00:52:56,780 --> 00:52:58,500
Trust in us.

657
00:53:04,560 --> 00:53:06,130
Thank you.

658
00:53:07,575 --> 00:53:11,230
Lu Zhi Shen,
you will lie in wait at the front.

659
00:53:11,230 --> 00:53:16,315
Chao Gai, we shall await
Ruan Xiao Wu's signal.

660
00:53:20,650 --> 00:53:23,000
They really came this way.

661
00:53:28,765 --> 00:53:31,820
At Ruan Xiao Wu's signal,
we will all take action at once.

662
00:53:31,820 --> 00:53:35,580
While the guards are distracted
by Lu Zhi Shen,

663
00:53:35,580 --> 00:53:39,255
Chao Gai will spring an attack from behind.

664
00:53:39,255 --> 00:53:40,825
Understood.

665
00:53:48,495 --> 00:53:50,100
What was that sound?

666
00:53:50,100 --> 00:53:52,020
Perhaps it was a signal?

667
00:53:52,020 --> 00:53:54,650
There! Someone is blocking the way!

668
00:53:54,650 --> 00:53:56,250
What are you doing here?

669
00:53:56,250 --> 00:53:58,800
I have come to take that man away!

670
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:00,175
Lu Zhi Shen...

671
00:54:00,175 --> 00:54:02,895
- Apprehend him!
- Yes, sir!

672
00:54:28,635 --> 00:54:31,700
A pincer with two men?

673
00:54:31,700 --> 00:54:35,580
They underestimate us!

674
00:54:55,480 --> 00:54:58,290
Stay hidden in the fronds, Wu Yong.

675
00:55:07,130 --> 00:55:09,760
Do not waste your lives!

676
00:55:13,939 --> 00:55:19,100
Ruan Xiao Wu! I hear you do better in water?

677
00:55:19,100 --> 00:55:21,160
You're damn right I do!

678
00:55:27,130 --> 00:55:31,250
<i>Please, save Lin Chong.</i>

679
00:55:40,600 --> 00:55:44,120
I have the captain's head!

680
00:55:49,920 --> 00:55:51,620
Lin Chong!

681
00:55:52,400 --> 00:55:54,280
Lin Chong!

682
00:55:55,460 --> 00:55:57,800
You're late.

683
00:55:58,810 --> 00:56:00,790
Lu Zhi Shen.

684
00:56:01,560 --> 00:56:03,380
I'm sorry, my friend!

685
00:56:16,815 --> 00:56:20,810
[Yuncheng Administrative Office]

686
00:56:20,810 --> 00:56:23,295
Song Jiang.

687
00:56:23,295 --> 00:56:25,895
Your head is in the clouds.

688
00:56:40,359 --> 00:56:43,650
If we could expose
just one fault of the government,

689
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:45,560
it would quickly spread like wildfire.

690
00:56:45,560 --> 00:56:48,440
I came to see you, An Dao Quan.

691
00:56:48,440 --> 00:56:50,230
"Yang Zhi, the Blue-faced Beast"?

692
00:56:50,230 --> 00:56:51,520
Not bad.

693
00:56:51,520 --> 00:56:53,600
I am alive within you.

694
00:56:53,600 --> 00:56:55,190
I believe it to be true.

695
00:56:55,190 --> 00:56:57,020
Saving Bai Sheng?

696
00:56:57,020 --> 00:56:59,270
We're breaking out.

697
00:56:59,270 --> 00:57:01,270
Do not cower! They will realize your lies.

698
00:57:01,270 --> 00:57:04,425
I would never lose.

699
00:57:04,425 --> 00:57:09,235
Has this invisible enemy of ours
noticed our presence?

700
00:58:53,500 --> 00:58:59,230
[Episode 2 - FIN]

